Merge pull request #418 from Bioinformatics/1.38

release 1.38

Canv 604 v2 (#416)

* Make wavelet scoring function depend on the (local) data mean, so that the fact that high-copy regions have higher absolute variance than low-copy regions doesn't lead to oversegmentation.  Also clean up some unnecessarily complex code and add a baby unit test.

* hack model distance penalty for high copy number

* revise coverage variability measurements (used in thresholding segmentation breakpoints)

* use coverage segmentation on all samples (even low-evenness ones, i.e. turn off VF segmentation)

* remove some of the bogus intermediate breakpoints from wavelet segmentation

* scale coverage variability measures by local median coverage

fix MAF value in CoverangeAndVariantFrequency file (#414)

* fix MAF value in CoverangeAndVariantFrequency file

Canv 673 low purity (#411)

* relabel cluster IDs for segments to reflect cluster pruning
* Modify MAF estimation when creating model points
* allow reduced minimum purity (<0.2) ... but only if there is strong support for CNVs (avoid low-purity interpretation of quiet tumor)
* tweak subscore weights to favor deviation more -- hack for DTB-008

Improvements to purity/ploidy estimation CANV-673 (#410)

* miscellaneous easy changes (#404)

* miscellaneous easy changes

* Add changes to make grid search finer-resolution and increase maximum ploidy (#405)

* CANV-673 scoring reorg (#407)

* modifications and reorganization to model scoring

* Canv 673 clustering (#408)

* add modified version of Accord framework MeanShift code
* modify clustering algorithm
* add LGPL to COPYRIGHT.txt for Accord libraries

* fix linq query
